title: Enhanced fragment emission in the interaction of 18.5 GeV 12C ions with complex nuclei

x4freetext: Enhanced fragment emission in the interaction of 18.5

x4freetext: The targets ranged in surface density from 10 mg/cm2
(Ag) to 80 mg/cm2 (U). The foils were surrounded by
Mylar catcher foils and individually encapsulated in
evacuated plastic bags along with three Al beam
monitor foils placed on the upstream side.
of metallic foils of the various target elements with
18.5 GeV 12C ions at the Bevalac and with 400 GeV
protons at Fermilab. The products of interest were
detected after bombardment by gamma-ray spectrometry.
The spectra were analyzed with the code SAMPO
in order to obtain the desired gamma-ray intensities.
The disintegration rates at end of bombardment were
obtained with the code CLSQ, and the cross sections
were obtained from these results and the Al beam
intensity monitor data after correction for recoil

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: tabulated cross sections are the larger of the
internal and external error. The former is based on
the uncertainty in the SAMPO and CLSQ fits and
includes an additional 5-10% uncertainty in the
magnitude of the various correction factors. The
external error is based on the agreement between the
results obtained on the basis of the various
gamma-rays assayed for a given nuclide in the
resulting from gamma-gamma coincidences. Finally, the
12C data were corrected by up to 2% for fluctuations
